# Azure Traffic Manager Profile - Terraform Module

This Terraform module deploys an Azure Traffic Manager Profile in Azure and optionally provisions traffic manager endpoints. The module provides a convenient way to deploy a Traffic Manager Profile with most commonly required configurations.

## Features

- Deploy Azure Traffic Manager Profile with different routing methods
- Configure monitor settings for endpoint health checks
- Add multiple endpoints of different types (Azure, External, Nested)
- Support for diagnostic settings
- Compatible with Azure Verified Modules (AVM) patterns

## Example Usage

```hcl
module "traffic_manager" {
  source              = "Azure/avm-res-network-trafficmanagerprofile/azurerm"
  version             = "~> 0.1.0"
  
  name                = "mytmprofile"
  resource_group_name = "my-resource-group"
  
  traffic_routing_method = "Priority"
  profile_status         = "Enabled"
  ttl                    = 60
  
  monitor_config = {
    protocol                     = "HTTP"
    port                         = 80
    path                         = "/"
    interval_in_seconds          = 30
    timeout_in_seconds           = 10
    tolerated_number_of_failures = 3
    expected_status_code_ranges  = ["200-299"]
  }
  
  endpoints = [
    {
      name               = "primary"
      endpoint_type      = "Azure"
      target_resource_id = azurerm_windows_web_app.example1.id
      priority           = 1
      endpoint_status    = "Enabled"
    },
    {
      name               = "secondary"
      endpoint_type      = "Azure"
      target_resource_id = azurerm_windows_web_app.example2.id
      priority           = 2
      endpoint_status    = "Enabled"
    }
  ]
  
  tags = {
    environment = "production"
    owner       = "terraform"
  }
}
```

