## Inputs

| Name | Description | Type | Default | Required |
|------|-------------|------|---------|:--------:|
| name | The name of the Traffic Manager profile. | string | n/a | yes |
| resource_group_name | The resource group where the resources will be deployed. | string | n/a | yes |
| location | Azure region where the resource should be deployed. | string | n/a | yes |
| traffic_routing_method | Specifies the traffic routing method of the Traffic Manager profile. Possible values are: Geographic, MultiValue, Performance, Priority, Subnet, Weighted. | string | "Performance" | no |
| profile_status | The status of the Traffic Manager profile. Possible values are: Enabled and Disabled. | string | "Enabled" | no |
| ttl | The DNS Time-To-Live (TTL), in seconds. Possible values include 30 to 999999. | number | 30 | no |
| monitor_config | The endpoint monitoring configuration of the Traffic Manager profile. | object | See variables.tf | no |
| max_return | The amount of endpoints to return for DNS queries to this Profile. Only valid for MultiValue routing method. | number | null | no |
| endpoints | List of Traffic Manager endpoints. | list(object) | [] | no |
| tags | Tags to be applied to resources. | map(string) | {} | no |
| diagnostic_settings | A map of diagnostic settings to create. | map(object) | {} | no |
| enable_telemetry | Enable telemetry via a Globally Unique Identifier (GUID). | bool | true | no |

## Outputs

| Name | Description |
|------|-------------|
| id | The ID of the Traffic Manager profile. |
| name | The name of the Traffic Manager profile. |
| resource_group_name | The name of the resource group in which the Traffic Manager profile is created. |
| fqdn | The fully qualified domain name of the Traffic Manager profile. |
| traffic_routing_method | The traffic routing method of the Traffic Manager profile. |
| profile_status | The status of the Traffic Manager profile. |
| endpoints | A map of Traffic Manager endpoints. |

